comment_data.body:
@scoder I've been looking with more detail into this.

If we follow your suggestion of using `body_ctx = Ctx(visibility=ctx.visibility)` (which I totally agree), then the check for visibility seems rather redundant: the Cython syntax simply does not allow a struct member to be declared with any visibility.

I believe the true branch of the original check never ever triggered. We have no test checking for the error. Moreover, I tried to come up with a test that would trigger the error, but I failed. Can you produce a test that would emit the error? Otherwise, maybe it is simpler to just remove the check as @matusvalo did previously?

